    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-12T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.34 Leasing/23a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Missions in Bolivia, Costa Rica, Cuba,
                            Dominican Republic, El Salvador, Guatemala, Haiti, Honduras, Nicaragua,
                            Panama, and Paraguay</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-12T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Here follows text the same as in circular of August 9, 6 p.m., <ref
                        target="#pg_151">page 151</ref>, with addition of paragraph here printed
                    inserted before final paragraph of that circular.]</p>
                <p>4. The proposed leases of destroyers would under no circumstances be made in such
                    instances or in such a manner as would serve to promote armaments races as among
                    nations or to stimulate the establishment of naval forces in those countries
                    which do not now have naval forces; nor would leases in any other respect be
                    made in a way that would be inconsistent with the principles for the maintenance
                    of peace and disarmament incorporated in the treaties, conventions and
                    resolutions of the Inter-American Conference for the Maintenance of Peace at
                    Buenos Aires,<note n="11" xml:id="d169fn11">See Department of State Conference
                        Series No. 33: <hi rend="italic">Report of the Delegation of the United
                            States of America to the Inter-American Conference for the Maintenance
                            of Peace, Buenos Aires, Argentina, December 1–23, 1936.</hi>
                    </note> and with the principles of this Government’s <pb facs="0168" n="158"
                        xml:id="pg_158"/> foreign policy which I had occasion to summarize in my
                    statement of July 16 last.<note n="12" xml:id="d169fn12">
                        <ref target="frus1937v01#pg_699">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            699</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
